item.title: Janelle add a quote by J.D. Salinger
item.description: "I'm sick of just liking people. I wish to God I could meet somebody I could respect." -- J.D. Salinger

item.title: Janelle add a quote by J. D. Salinger
item.description: "Don't ever tell anybody anything. If you do, you start missing everybody." -- J. D. Salinger

item.title: Janelle add a quote by J.D. Salinger
item.description: "I'm a kind of paranoiac in reverse. I suspect people of plotting to make me happy." -- J.D. Salinger

item.title: Janelle add a quote by J.D. Salinger
item.description: "The fact is always obvious much too late, but the most singular difference between happiness and joy is that happiness is a solid and joy a liquid." -- J.D. Salinger

item.title: Janelle add a quote by J.D. Salinger
item.description: "I'm sick of not having the courage to be an absolute nobody." -- J.D. Salinger

item.title: Janelle add a quote by J.D. Salinger
item.description: "I'm the most terrific liar you ever saw in your life. It's awful. If I'm on my way to the store to buy a magazine, even, and somebody asks me where I'm going, I'm liable to say I'm going to the opera. It's terrible." -- J.D. Salinger

item.title: Janelle add a quote by J.D. Salinger
item.description: "It's funny. All you have to do is say something nobody understands and they'll do practically anything you want them to." -- J.D. Salinger

item.title: Janelle add a quote by J.D. Salinger
item.description: "An artist's only concern is to shoot for some kind of perfection, and on his own terms, not anyone else's." -- J.D. Salinger

item.title: Janelle add a quote by J.D. Salinger
item.description: "I’m just sick of ego, ego, ego. My own and everybody else’s. I’m sick of everybody that wants to get somewhere, do something distinguished and all, be somebody interesting. It’s disgusting." -- J.D. Salinger

item.title: Janelle add a quote by Lemony Snicket
item.description: "Never trust anyone who has not brought a book with them." -- Lemony Snicket

item.title: Janelle add a quote by Lemony Snicket
item.description: "People aren't either wicked or noble. They're like chef's salads, with good things and bad things chopped and mixed together in a vinaigrette of confusion and conflict." -- Lemony Snicket

item.title: Janelle add a quote by Lemony Snicket
item.description: "Fate is like a strange, unpopular restaurant filled with odd little waiters who bring you things you never asked for and don't always like." -- Lemony Snicket

item.title: Janelle add a quote by Lemony Snicket
item.description: "Wicked people never have time for reading. It's one of the reasons for their wickedness." -- Lemony Snicket

item.title: Janelle add a quote by Lemony Snicket
item.description: "Reading is one form of escape. Running for your life is another." -- Lemony Snicket

item.title: Janelle add a quote by Lemony Snicket
item.description: "A good library will never be too neat, or too dusty, because somebody will always be in it, taking books off the shelves and staying up late reading them." -- Lemony Snicket

item.title: Janelle add a quote by Lemony Snicket
item.description: "No matter who you are, no matter where you live, and no matter how many people are chasing you, what you don't read is often as important as what you do read." -- Lemony Snicket

item.title: Janelle add a quote by Lemony Snicket
item.description: "Well-read people are less likely to be evil." -- Lemony Snicket

item.title: Janelle add a quote by David Levithan
item.description: "Love weaves itself from hundreds of threads." -- David Levithan

item.title: Janelle add a quote by David Levithan
item.description: "We'd said we'd keep in touch. But touch is not something you can keep; as soon as it's gone, it's gone. We should have said we'd keep in words, because they are all we can string between us--words on a telephone line, words appearing on a screen." -- David Levithan

item.title: Janelle add a quote by David Levithan
item.description: "It doesn't have to be on Valentine's Day. It doesn't have to be by the time you turn eighteen or thirty-three or fifty-nine. It doesn't have to conform to whatever is usual. It doesn't have to be kismet at once, or rhapsody by the third date. It just has to be. In time. In place. In spirit. It just has to be." -- David Levithan

item.title: Janelle add a quote by David Levithan
item.description: "To love--to fall--is not a question. To touch--to kiss--to speak--those are questions." -- David Levithan

item.title: Janelle add a quote by David Levithan
item.description: "Here’s what I know about the realm of possibility— it is always expanding, it is never what you think it is. Everything around us was once deemed impossible. From the airplane overhead to the phones in our pockets to the choir girl putting her arm around the metalhead. As hard as it is for us to see sometimes, we all exist within the realm of possibility. Most of the limits are of our own world’s devising. And yet, every day we each do so many things that were once impossible to us. " -- David Levithan

item.title: Janelle add a quote by David Levithan
item.description:
"I want to write my life. I want to be able to write my life.
You are a second away from saying it.
You have no idea how much I love you." -- David Levithan

item.title: Janelle add a quote by David Levithan
item.description: "Maybe that's it, [...] [w]ith what you were talking about before. The world being broken. Maybe it isn't that we're supposed to find the pieces and put them back together. Maybe <i>we're</i> the pieces." [...] "Maybe [...] what we're supposed to do is come together. That's how we stop the breaking." -- David Levithan

item.title: Janelle add a quote by David Levithan
item.description: "To get something you must give something away. To hold something you must give something away. To love something you must give something away." -- David Levithan

item.title: Janelle add a quote by Lemony Snicket
item.description: "All the secrets of the world are contained in books. Read at your own risk." -- Lemony Snicket

item.title: Janelle add a quote by J.D. Salinger
item.description: "Grand. There's a word I really hate. It's a phony. I could puke every time I hear it." -- J.D. Salinger

item.title: Janelle add a quote by J.D. Salinger
item.description: "I don't really deeply feel that anyone needs an airtight reason for quoting from the works of the writers he loves, but it's always nice, I'll grant you, if he has one." -- J.D. Salinger

item.title: Janelle add a quote by J.D. Salinger
item.description: "She wrote to him fairly regularly, from a paradise of triple exclamation points and inaccurate observations." -- J.D. Salinger

item.title: Janelle add a quote by John Green
item.description: "What a treacherous thing to believe that a person is more than a person." -- John Green
